The paper discusses achieving strong consistency in distributed systems while minimizing communication between nodes, which is a common problem in distributed computing. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses data consistency, which is a common topic in the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper uses program analysis to extract semantic information, which suggests that it could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses a homeostasis protocol, which is a common topic in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses optimizing treaties based on workload characteristics, which suggests that it could belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
